Structural Divergence Analysis

Maria Laura Marcos, Julian Echave

Introduction

In this case we studied the sh3 family. We used as reference for the ENM the protein with pdb code 1lcka. We simulated 10 mutants of this reference for each protein of the family. The sh3 family is of the type small beta and consists of the following proteins:

##  [1] "1shg"   "1shfa"  "2src"   "1qcfa"  "1qlya"  "1bbza"  "1gria1"
##  [8] "1gbra"  "1cska"  "1ckaa"  "1sema"  "1gria2" "1ycsb"  "2hsp"  
## [15] "1ark"   "1aoja"  "1pht"   "1bb9"   "1awj"
